docs {
  # Restore Note
  Restore a soft-deleted note to make it active again.

  ## Authentication
  Required: Bearer token (JWT)

  ## Path Parameters
  - **id** (required): The ID of the soft-deleted note to restore

  ## Response Format
  ```json
  {
    "success": true,
    "data": {
      "id": 1,
      "user_id": 1,
      "parent_id": null,
      "title": "Meeting Notes",
      "icon": "üìù",
      "cover_image": "",
      "blocks": [],
      "view_metadata": null,
      "properties": {},
      "path": "/1",
      "depth": 0,
      "position": 0,
      "is_archived": false,
      "is_deleted": false,
      "created_at": "2025-12-30T10:00:00Z",
      "updated_at": "2025-12-30T13:00:00Z"
    }
  }
  ```

  ## Restore Behavior
  - Sets `is_deleted: false` flag
  - Makes soft-deleted note visible again
  - Restores all child notes as well
  - Preserves all note content and metadata
  - Can only restore notes deleted via soft delete (DELETE endpoint)

  ## Error Responses

  ### 404 Not Found
  ```json
  {
    "error": "note not found"
  }
  ```

  ### 403 Forbidden
  ```json
  {
    "error": "access denied"
  }
  ```

  ## Status Codes
  - **200 OK**: Note successfully restored
  - **400 Bad Request**: Invalid note ID
  - **401 Unauthorized**: Missing or invalid authentication
  - **403 Forbidden**: Access denied to note
  - **404 Not Found**: Note not found (or already deleted permanently)
  - **500 Internal Server Error**: Server error

  ## Related Endpoints
  - DELETE /api/v1/notes/:id - Soft delete a note
}
